❤️‍🔥 CARBON DATING UPDATE! ❤️‍🔥 This past summer, you may remember that we launched a fundraising campaign for our short film, Carbon Dating. Because of the generosity of so many of you, our team of ten was able to spend four days in Joshua Tree, CA bringing this imaginary, dystopian world to life. 🏜️

To say it was a magical week is an understatement. We got to see an idea that only existed in our minds materialize in the physical realm and to relish in the intoxicating experience of creative collaboration on a project we all felt a connection to. 

Since we wrapped filming in August, we’ve spent the last few months hustling to edit the film in order to submit to film festivals. It's been a ton of hard (but incredibly fulfilling) work. Now, we patiently await their feedback. Our dream is to premiere Carbon Dating at one of these festivals in 2023 and then release it online for everyone to enjoy. 

If you were able to donate to the making of this film, we CANNOT thank you enough for your donation. Without it, none of this would have been possible. You not only empowered us to create something original and meaningful, but to fulfill a dream that has been years in the making. Your generosity has been a gift with a lasting impact on all of our lives and creative careers. 

And for those that shared, commented, cheered on the project, and have been inquiring about its status since -- your enthusiasm means the world. We can't wait to share it with you, and we'll keep you updated when we can. 🧡

In the meantime, please enjoy these stills from the film -- can you BELIEVE our DP caught that lightning strike?! 🌩️

HAPPY RUNE-IVERSARY TO ALL WHO WISH TO CELEBRATE (it’s me, hi). 

Two years ago on Jan 12, I posted the first video of what I didn’t know would become “The Rune Series.”

I concluded the fourth season of it last March and the question remains: Did I choose the Rune characters or did they choose me? In many ways, I feel like they landed in me like past lives, projected a self-appointed quest on the floor in front of me, ushered me through to…something. Perhaps the cosmos within. 

Or maybe it really was just a random idea that hit an algorithm at just the right moment when everyone was too bored and sad to be looking anywhere else — an elaborate result of my own escapism, a luminous way to cope.

Either way, The Rune Series is the best-worst thing I’ve ever made. I am so proud of it and so delightfully embarrassed by it. It is me at my peak cringe. But okay, then. Fine. Let it be that. Maybe our fear of being cringe is really just our fear of creative risk, the gamble of being witnessed while fully committing to something. 

And, my god, did I commit to Rune with my whole chest. My god, did I lose the thread on that one — that series that began “as a joke.” 

And on that note, yes, Rune is a parody series. I use a Christmas ornament as a “pyrochasm”. The plot is a series of cheap tricks that only really makes sense if you close one eye and hum an E flat while you listen. All my characters have winged eyeliner because it’s the only look I know how to do. 

It’s a parody, of course, but it isn’t a joke. It was never a joke. 

Unless, of course, the joke was on me—thinking I could hide behind a trope, thinking I was clever enough to circumvent sincerity. I tried to trick the muse, tried to tiptoe around the thing I loved…until eventually, I got so close, I just became it. 

Anyway, if you want to binge the first two seasons, they’re up on YooooTü🅱️e. And please subscribe if you like! 

Because the Rune-iverse has more stories to tell. Soon. (♑️💙♓️)

Tl;dr: I fucking love The Rune Series. First two seasons are up on YooooToooo🅱️ if you wanna rewatch / binge / have no idea what I’m talking about. More to come. 

Til then, through the airwaves…♊️✨🌌💫

Some moments on the way to completing my first lil YouTube series! For everyone asking how many takes it took Phil to say “DREADED REJECTION REDEMPTION & RESURRECTION III” — slide 2 is for you. 🎮 And yes, casting timed my dog’s grooming appointment so he could play two different dogs in the series. 🐕🐩

What a learning curve it’s been to expand in this way. My cells always buzz at the challenge and the humble, wobbly-legged feeling of trying something new. I always find that if you can just get that first one outta your system — that’s the key. Gotta code the possibility into your cells. Gotta just try. Begin. Find out. 

I’ll still be putting out my usual stuff here but if you’ve ever said “I’m invested and need more” my YT channel will be for you. Thank you to everyone who’s found me there and for being here to enjoy these silly little worlds 💛💛💛 All 3 parts of the dog park rom-com are up! 🎾💕🐾🐕🎮🕶️

Pressalike Productions casually delivering the biggest plot twist of my life 🤯

There comes a point in every artist’s life where 60 seconds worth of chemistry with yourself just isn’t enough, so I’ve been working hard under Pressalike’s legendary guidance to expand fan-favorite stories and characters for YouTube…and to bring some new ones to life. 

Thank you to @anthonypadilla and Alessandra Catanese (@alecat22) at Pressalike for recognizing the spark of creative joy at the heart of every video and generously deciding to support the expansion of it. 

Thank you to KathySue Holtorf (@kathysue17) and Mallory Myers (@mal_myerz) from Pressalike’s team for your brilliance, patience, and expertise and making me feel like no question is too silly to ask.

Thank you to my manager, Kevin Herrera, @jointhemachine who set this in motion and made me and my creative vision feel seen and understood from our very first meeting. And to my friend @sandrakateburck for altering my destiny and connecting me to Kevin. 

And to every single one of you: oh my god. Thank you. For engaging in my videos over the past few years, for delighting in the characters with me, sharing them with your friends, and leaning into the cringeworthy levels of commitment. You’ve helped celebrate a part of myself and my creative expression I’ve been afraid to embrace for a very, very long time.

Also please subscribe to my YT channel (lol). New things SOONSOONSOON!

I found @parade years ago when I was ready to leave the cult of over-stuffed and under-serving push-up bras. They just didn’t feel like me anymore, and I needed something new to believe in: a bralette that supported my big creative lifestyle...and fit my small chest. 🫧

I asked (googled) 💫. And Parade delivered 💝.

Parade’s pieces spoke for themselves in comfort and sustainability, but they really sealed the deal with me when I learned how committed their team is to being inclusive. As someone who feels like they’re constantly transforming (hello, Scorpio rising!), I’m a big believer in the fact that we aren’t just one thing (nor should we have to be) — and something as essential and personal as our underwear should support us in that. 

🎪 Lucky for us, Parade is extending their Summer Sale, and ONLY my code CAROLINE50 gets you 50% OFF the entire site. Click the link yourparade.com/CAROLINE50 under my linktree for 50% OFF site-wide! 🎪

People ask what we’d tell our 15 year-old selves, as if our 15 year-old selves wouldn’t all be annoyed af to have to talk to us, let alone listen to us dispense dewy-eyed advice. So I think I’d just let her know that when the party tent behind us played Grand Theft Autumn/Where Is Your Boy Tonight, I still knew every word and that the company I was with could all agree that nothing went harder than the lyric ⛱️🎸U WERE THE LAST GOOD THING ABOUT THIS PART OF TOWN🎸⛱️. I’d tell her we still got in the ocean, and the dog fell asleep on the drive home. I’d leave out that I was listening to a re-recorded version of Speak Now because that’s a lot to explain, and I’m already losing her attention to an incoming text. Idk. I don’t think she’d be impressed. But I do think it’d be enough for her to know things turned out okay.
